SIMPLE: wearer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wearer
<hw>Wear"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
wears or carries as appendant to the body; <as>as, the <ex>wearer</ex>
of a cloak, a sword, a crown, a shackle, etc</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Cowls, hoods, and habits, with their <qex>wearers</qex>,
tossed,⟦br⟧
And fluttered into rags.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which wastes or diminishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weariable</ent>⟦br⟧
